# Build and Test Quickstart

Recommended CMake flow:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DQTLUCIDE_BUILD_TESTS=ON -DQTLUCIDE_BUILD_EXAMPLES=ON
cmake --build build -j
ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure
```

Alternative Meson flow:

```bash
meson setup builddir_meson -Dtests=true -Dexamples=true
meson compile -C builddir_meson
meson test -C builddir_meson
```

Unified helper scripts:

- Windows: [`scripts/build.bat`](mdc:scripts/build.bat) (e.g., `scripts\build.bat --test`)
- Cross-platform Python: [`scripts/build.py`](mdc:scripts/build.py) (e.g., `python3 scripts/build.py --test`)

Resources regeneration is handled automatically in CMake builds via [`build_all_resources.py`](mdc:build_all_resources.py). You can run it manually when modifying icons or metadata.
